## OpenClaw Upstream — Memory Conventions

**File model** (`docs/concepts/memory.md`):

> "MEMORY.md … long-term memory. Durable facts, preferences, and decisions. Loaded at the start of every DM session."
> "memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md … Today and yesterday's notes are loaded automatically."
> "DREAMS.md … Dream Diary and dreaming sweep summaries for human review."
> "The model only 'remembers' what gets saved to disk -- there is no hidden state."

**Tool surface:** `memory_search` (hybrid) + `memory_get` (file/line read). Plugin entry-point: `memory-core` by default; alt `qmd`, `honcho`.

**CLI:** `openclaw memory status | search "q" | index --force`.

**Config keys** (`docs/reference/memory-config.md`):
```
memorySearch.query.hybrid.vectorWeight = 0.7
memorySearch.query.hybrid.textWeight   = 0.3
memorySearch.query.hybrid.candidateMultiplier = 4
memorySearch.query.mmr.enabled = false   ; lambda 0.7
memorySearch.query.temporalDecay.enabled = false   ; halfLifeDays 30
memorySearch.cache.enabled = false       ; maxEntries 50000
plugins.entries.memory-core.config.dreaming.enabled = false
plugins.entries.memory-core.config.dreaming.frequency = "0 3 * * *"
```
Note: MMR and temporalDecay are **off by default** — most users get raw hybrid only.

**Open issues to know about:**
- #66947 — Dreaming writes Light/REM into `memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md`, causing heartbeat agents to skip logging because "today's file already exists". Default `storage.mode="inline"` is the culprit; `"separate"` mode + `memory/dreaming/<phase>/…` already exists. **Not yet fixed upstream.**
- #62184 — Proposal for `learning_candidates` staging slot for explicit corrections. **Closed: not planned.**
- #65630 — Dreaming and Supermemory compete for the same memory-extension slot; can't run both. Open.
- #19760 — Built-in MMR diversity rerank for memory search. Open.

---

## State of the Art (2026)

### Letta / MemGPT
- Three-tier OS-style memory: **Core** (always-in-context, RAM-like), **Recall** (searchable conversation history), **Archival** (vector store, queried via `archival_memory_search`).
- Agent **self-edits** memory via tool calls — decides what to keep, demote, archive.
- Re-architected agent loop in 2026 v1 borrows from ReAct and Claude Code; stateful by default, runs via Letta server.
- DMR benchmark baseline that newer systems target.
- MIT OSS at `letta-ai/letta`; managed cloud also available.

### Mem0
- "Memory layer" SDK; multi-signal retrieval (semantic + BM25 + entity boost), fused in parallel.
- Pro tier adds **graph memory** on top of vector+KV — entities linked across memories for relational recall.
- Token-efficient algorithm benchmarked in arxiv 2504.19413; reports lower context cost vs raw RAG.
- 21 framework integrations, 19 vector stores, 3 hosting models (cloud/self-host/local-MCP).
- Recommended embedding floor: Qwen-600M class.

### Zep / Graphiti
- **Temporal knowledge graph** for agent memory; three subgraphs: episode, semantic-entity, community.
- Validity windows on facts — old facts invalidated, not deleted; supports "what was true at T".
- 94.8% on DMR (vs MemGPT 93.4%); +18.5% accuracy with -90% latency on baseline RAG.
- Graphiti is OSS; Zep Cloud is the managed product.
- Strong fit when "who-did-what-when" matters more than vector recall.

### A-MEM (NeurIPS 2025)
- Zettelkasten-inspired: each memory is an **atomic note** with content, timestamp, LLM-keywords, LLM-tags, contextual description, embedding, and **links**.
- Memory **evolves**: adding a new note can rewrite the descriptions/tags of linked older notes.
- No predetermined ops — agent itself organizes the network.
- Beats SOTA on 6 foundation models on long-context QA.
- Code: `agiresearch/A-mem` (paper authors) + `WujiangXu/A-mem`.

### LangMem (LangChain)
- Memory primitives — **Memory Manager** + **Prompt Optimizer** — designed as functional building blocks (no side effects).
- **Reflective consolidation:** background job revisits memories, merges duplicates, overrides stale facts, summarizes old conversations.
- Three prompt-update algorithms: `metaprompt`, `gradient` (critique-then-propose), `prompt_memory` (single-shot).
- "Subconscious" formation pattern: reflect after conversation ends, not during the hot path.
- Pairs with LangGraph for orchestration; OSS at `langchain-ai/langmem`.

### Cognee
- **Extract → Cognify → Load** pipeline: raw → normalized docs → KG-with-embeddings → searchable.
- Builds entity/relation graphs (e.g. `opened_ticket`, `resolved_by`) instead of doc-chunk RAG.
- Search modes: `GRAPH_COMPLETION` (LLM reasons over graph), `RAG_COMPLETION` (chunks), and specialized.
- MCP server available (`cognee-mcp`) so any MCP client can use it.
- "6 lines of code" install pitch; works with Memgraph / Neo4j / others.

### Goose Memory (Block / AAIF)
- Built-in extension; stores per-project (local) and universal (global) facts.
- Trigger-word detection ("remember…", "save this") for capture; auto-suggests saving on detected patterns.
- Markdown-flat, similar to OpenClaw's MEMORY.md ethos but with named scopes.
- Now under Linux Foundation's Agentic AI Foundation (AAIF).

### Claude Code Auto-Memory
- Two files: **CLAUDE.md** (your instructions) + **MEMORY.md** (Claude's notebook about you).
- Hard rule: **first 200 lines of MEMORY.md are loaded; rest is invisible.** Larger files reduce adherence.
- Auto-spillover: when topic-notes pile up, Claude moves them to dedicated files (`debugging.md`, `patterns.md`).
- Uses heuristics on whether the info will be useful in *future* sessions before saving.
- "Auto Dream" consolidation feature periodically reorganizes auto-memory.

